.TH PRINTF 3 "November 2024" "Holberton School" "Manual for the _printf function"

.SH NAME
_printf \- custom implementation of the printf function

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <main.h>
.br
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf
function produces output according to a format string, similarly to the standard printf function in C.

.PP
The format string contains fixed text and format specifiers, which serve as placeholders for the variables provided as additional arguments. Supported specifiers include:

.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.

.TP
.B %s
Prints a string of characters.

.TP
.B %%
Prints a percentage sign.

.TP
.B %d
Prints a signed decimal integer.

.TP
.B %i
Prints a signed decimal integer (identical to %d).

.PP
Undefined behavior occurs if the format string contains unsupported specifiers or if insufficient arguments are provided to match the specifiers.

.SH PARAMETERS
.TP
.B format
A format string containing fixed text and format specifiers. This string must be null-terminated (`\0`).

.TP
.B ...
Additional arguments that will replace the format specifiers in the format string.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.B _printf
function returns the number of characters printed (excluding the null byte used to end output to strings).
In case of an error, it returns a negative value.

.SH EXAMPLES
Basic usage example:
.PP
.nf
#include <main.h>
.br
int main(void) {
.br
    _printf("Hello, %s!\n", "world");
.br
    _printf("The number is: %d\n", 42);
.br
    return (0);
}
.fi

Output of the example:
.PP
Hello, world!
.br
The number is: 42

.SH LIMITATIONS
Currently, the implementation of
.B _printf
does not support:
.PP
- Flags such as `+`, ` `, or `#`.
.br
- Field width or precision.
.br
- Length modifiers such as `l` or `h`.

.SH SEE ALSO
.B printf(3),
.B write(2)

.SH AUTHOR
Developed by:
.PP
- Adolfo Rodriguez: Lead developer of the `_printf` function, core logic, and the implementation of `%c`, `%s`, and `%%` specifiers.
.PP
- Carlos Valentin: Developer of the `%d` and `%i` specifiers and author of the README.md documentation.

